author: djames
msg: Update svnserve to avoid unnecessary path calculations when path-based
authorization is disabled. This change reduces the time required to run
'svn log' on a revision with 10,000 paths from 7 seconds to 0.2 seconds,
if you are using the BDB backend. (If you are using FSFS, the performance
difference will be less dramatic, because FSFS is already quite fast.)
* subversion/svnserve/serve.c
(authz_check_access_cb_func): New function. If authz is enabled, returns an
authz callback. Otherwise, returns NULL.
(accept_report, change_rev_prop, rev_proplist, rev_prop, log_cmd,
get_locations, get_file_revs, get_locks, replay): Use
authz_check_access_cb_func to get our authz callback.
